name: score
desc:
The raw value returned by the service without applying any thresholds or comparison rules.
The value shows the degree of similarity of compared faces, the lower - the more similar, and vice versa less similar.
The score is used in conjunction with the input image imageType to evaluate similarity.

name: onlyCentralFace
desc:
Whether to process only the central face on the image or all the faces.
If set to true, the SDK detects and processes only one—the most central face in the image.
If set to false, the SDK processes all faces in the image.
Default is false.

name: ImageQualityGroup
desc: Image Quality characteristic group

name: background
desc:
The Background characteristics group checks the background uniformity,
shadows on background, and other faces presence on the picture.

name: eyes
desc:
The Eyes characteristics group checks eyes closure, occlusion, hair coverage,
red eye effect, and whether a person is looking directly at the camera.

name: faceImage
desc:
The Face image quality group includes blur and noise levels, unnatural skin tone,
and face dynamic range checks.

name: headOcclusion
desc: The Head occlusion group includes checks of glasses, face occlusion, and head coverage.

name: headSizeAndPosition
desc:
The Head size and position group includes the position of the "middle point"
relative to the width and height of the image, the head width to the image
width and height ratio, inter-eye distance, yaw, pitch, roll.

name: image
desc:
The Image characteristics group includes width, height, width to height proportions,
the image RGB channels number, and padding ratio.

name: poseAndExpression
desc:
The Pose and expression characteristics group checks the shoulders pose,
face expression, whether there is an open mouth or smile.

name: shadowsAndLightning
desc:
The Shadows and lightning characteristics group checks whether a photo
is too dark or overexposed, if there are glares or shadows on the face.

name: LivenessConfig
desc:
Configuration for the Liveness processing.
The configuration provides convenient properties to change the behavior and the appearance of the Liveness UI module.

name: attemptsCount
desc:
The number of attempts to pass the Liveness before completing with error. Defaults to 0.
When set to 0  the Liveness will always ask to retry on error.

name: cameraPositionAndroid
desc: Android only.

name: cameraPositionIOS
desc: IOS only.

name: cameraSwitchEnabled
desc:
Defines, whether the camera's toolbar switch camera button is available on the Liveness UI. Defaults to false.
When set to true the CameraToolbarView will contain a button to change current cameraPosition.
Only for livenessType = LivenessType.PASSIVE.

name: copyright
desc: Defines, whether the logo is visible on the bottom of Liveness UI screens. Defaults to true.

name: livenessType
desc: Defines whether the liveness processing type. Defaults to LivenessType.ACTIVE.

name: locationTrackingEnabled
desc:
Defines whether the liveness request sends a location of a device. Defaults to true.
When set to true the liveness request to web service will contain the location
object within the json metadata object.
The location is used only when permissions are granted and the location is available.

name: recordingProcess
desc:
Defines whether the liveness recording video of processing.
Defaults to RecordingProcess.ASYNCHRONOUS_UPLOAD.

name: screenOrientation
desc: Android only.

name: skipStep
desc: Defines which steps of the user interface can be omitted. See LivenessSkipStep enum for details.

name: tag
desc: Defines tag that can be used in Liveness processing. Defaults to null.

name: torchButtonEnabled
desc:
Defines, whether the camera's toolbar torch button is available on the Liveness UI. Defaults to true.
When set to false the CameraToolbarView won't contain a button to toggle camera's flashlight.
Only for livenessType = LivenessType.PASSIVE.

name: vibrateOnSteps
desc: Enables vibration during Liveness processing. Defaults to true.

name: faceRect
desc: Rectangular area of the detected face in the original image.

name: landmarks
desc: Main coordinates of the detected face (eyes, nose, lips, ears and etc.).

desc:
Coordinates of the rectangle with the face on the original image prepared for the face crop.
Requires OutputImageCrop.returnOriginalRect is set.
Returns null if OutputImageCrop.returnOriginalRect isn't set.

name: rotationAngle
desc:
Rotation is measured counterclockwise in degrees, with zero indicating
that a line drawn between the eyes is horizontal relative to the image orientation.

name: MatchFacesImage
desc: This class represents the input image and its attributes for MatchFacesRequest.

name: detectAll
desc:
Defines whether the comparison and detection should apply for all faces found on the image. Defaults to false.
When set to false, only the most centered faces are compared and detected.
Otherwise, all the faces are compared and detected.

name: image
desc: The underlying image.

name: imageType
desc:
The image type.
The imageType influences matching results, therefore this field is required.

name: MatchFacesRequest
desc:
Compares two or more images with faces on them to find out the similarity of pairs.
The request is used as a parameter to FaceSDK.matchFaces.

name: images
desc: Images with faces to match.

name: outputImageParams
desc: If set the uploaded image is processed according to the indicated settings.

name: tag
desc: Defines tag that can be used in match faces processing. Defaults to null.

name: MatchFacesResponse
desc: The response from the MatchFacesRequest.

name: detections
desc: Face detection results for each given image.

name: error
desc: The error describes a failed match faces request and contains MatchFacesErrorCode codes.

name: results
desc: Face comparison results with score and similarity values.

name: OutputImageCrop
desc: Crop settings for OutputImageParams.

name: padColor
desc:
When an image is aligned by type, its original size may be insufficient, and in this case it needs to be supplemented, "padded".
padColor sets the value for the color that will be used for such a supplement.

name: returnOriginalRect
desc:
If set, the coordinates of the rectangle with the face in the original image prepared for the face crop
are returned in the DetectFaceResult.originalRect field.
Default is false.

name: size
desc:
The resize value to process.
If the value doesn't match AspectRatio type proportion or minimum size, an adjustment is applied.
Use OutputImageCropAspectRatio to check you size matches AspectRatio type proportions and minimum size.

name: type
desc: The aspect ratio according to which alignment is performed.

name: OutputImageCropAspectRatio
desc: The AspectRatio according to which alignment is performed

name: values
desc: A constant List of the values in this enum, in order of their declaration.

name: OutputImageParams
desc: Set of parameter for image processing.

name: backgroundColor
desc:
If set, the background color is replaced.
The silhouette of a person is cut out and the background is filled with this color.

name: crop
desc:
If set, the Base64 of an aligned and cropped portrait is returned in the crop field.
Alignment is performed according to type.
If a head on the original image is tilted, for the returned portrait it is aligned in a straight vertical line.
